17
(9) One (1) representative of the department of environmental
management, who serves as a nonvoting member.
(10) The fertilizer administrator for the office of the state chemist,
who serves as a nonvoting member.
(11) The engineer specialist for the office of the state chemist,
who serves as a nonvoting member.
(12) One (1) representative of the Indiana state department of
agriculture, who shall serve as a nonvoting member.
(c) The state chemist shall appoint the voting members of the board,
