SECTION 37. IC 15-16-2-49.5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.81-2009,
SECTION 31, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 49.5. (a) If a person violates this chapter or a rule
adopted under this chapter, the state chemist may:
(1) warn, issue a citation to, or impose a civil penalty on the
person; or
(2) deny, suspend, revoke, or amend the person's registration
under this chapter;
(3) refer the person for criminal prosecution; or
(4) refer the person to another appropriate governmental
agency.
However, nothing in this chapter requires the state chemist to
impose a civil penalty for a violation.
(b) The state chemist shall adopt by rule, under IC 4-22-2, a
schedule of civil penalties that may be imposed under subsection (a).
The state chemist may impose a civil penalty only according to a the
schedule of civil penalties recommended by the board. in section 49.6
of this chapter.
(c) A person who knowingly or intentionally violates this chapter
commits a Class A misdemeanor.
